<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Dissuade" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Dissuade,</orth> 1) to divert by reasons: <cit><quote>I would fain d. him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.170" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 2, 170</bibl></cit>. With <cit><quote>from:</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 141.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 141, 10</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.171" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.147" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 147</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.215" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 215</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.1.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 1, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.463" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 463</bibl>.<lb />2) to speak against, to counteract: <cit><quote>example cannot for all that d. succession,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 3.5.25" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 5, 25</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>